Let $(\overline{M}^{n+k}, \overline{g})$ be a Riemannian manifold and let $M^{n} \subset \overline{M}^{n+k}$ be an isometrically immersed submanifold with induced metric $g$. Denote by $\overline{
abla}$ the Levi-Civita connection of $(\overline{M}, \overline{g})$ and by $B$ the second fundamental form defined by $B(X,Y) := (\overline{
abla}_{X}Y)^{\perp}$, where $X,Y \in \Gamma(TM)$ and $(\cdot)^{\perp}$ denotes orthogonal projection onto the normal bundle $NM$. For $\xi \in \Gamma(NM)$, define the shape operator $A_{\xi} \colon TM 	o TM$ by the identity $\langle B(X,Y), \xi angle = \langle A_{\xi}X, Y angle$, where $\langle \cdot, \cdot angle$ is the induced metric on $TM$. Fix a point $p \in M$, and choose orthonormal frames $\{e_{1},\dots,e_{n}\}$ for $T_{p}M$ and $\{\xi_{1},\dots,\xi_{k}\}$ for $N_{p}M$. Define the components $h_{ij}^{\alpha} := \langle B(e_{i}, e_{j}), \xi_{\alpha} angle$ at $p$.

Using only the fundamental definitions above and the orthonormality of the chosen frames, derive a closed-form expression for the squared norm $|B|^{2}(p)$ in terms of the components $h_{ij}^{\alpha}$. Then specialize to codimension one (so $k=1$) in dimension $n=2$. In this case, let $
u$ be the unit normal so that $A_{
u}$ is the corresponding shape operator at $p$. Express $|B|^{2}(p)$ entirely in terms of the trace and determinant of $A_{
u}$ at $p$. Provide your final answer as a single analytic expression for $|B|^{2}(p)$ that depends only on $\operatorname{tr}(A_{
u})$ and $\det(A_{
u})$. No rounding is required.
